STEPS :

$git clone https://github.com/pytorch/glow.git
$cd glow

$git submodule update --init --recursive

$sudo apt-get install clang clang-6.0 cmake graphviz libpng-dev \
    libprotobuf-dev llvm-6.0 ninja-build protobuf-compiler wget \
    opencl-headers libgoogle-glog-dev
    
$sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/clang clang \
    /usr/lib/llvm-6.0/bin/clang 50
$sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/clang++ clang++ \
    /usr/lib/llvm-6.0/bin/clang++ 50
    
$sudo update-alternatives --config cc
    # Select the option corresponding to /usr/bin/clang ...
$sudo update-alternatives --config c++
    # Select the option corresponding to /usr/bin/clang++ ...

Since llvm6 is installed, we need to build llvm : use command (in glow directory):

$./utils/build_llvm.sh

Now llvm 8.0 is built and stored in : /home/raj/glow/llvm_install/lib/cmake/llvm

Now, In home directory (not in glow directory) make a new build_debug directory :    
mkdir build_Debug
cd build_Debug


Then make the build file with following configuration : (release mode selected here and LLVM directory created) 

cmake -G Ninja ../glow \-DGLOW_MODELS_DIR=/home/raj/builds/models \-DGLOW_WITH_OPENCL=OFF \-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \-DBUILD_DOCS=ON \-DLLVM_DIR=/home/raj/glow/llvm_install/lib/cmake/llvm

Once this is successful, check all files for errors :

ninja all

Next comes mnist and all datasets :

Download datasets using this (in glow directory):
python ../glow/utils/download_test_db.py --all

Now run examples :

